@using ValueScreener.Controllers.Screeners
<br />
<h1>All Screeners</h1>
<br />


<div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingOne">
            <h2 class="panel-title">
                <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                    Net-Net Screener
                </a>
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>
                    Popularized by Benjamin Graham, the father of Value Investing, Net-Net stocks are stocks quoting aignificantly below their Net Current Asset Value, or NCAV.
                    The NCAV of a company is determined by looking at the balance sheet, taking the total current assets, and substracting the total liabilities.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Concretely, it means that if the company ceases its activity and pays all its debts, the cash remaining is still greater than the price quoted by the market. And you receive for free all the long term assets : Properties, Factories, Machinery...

                </p>
                <p>
                    Graham recommanded to buy stocks quoting at a discount of at least 30% of their Net Current Asset Value.
                </p>
                <h2>
                    <a style="text-decoration: none" asp-controller="Screener" asp-action="Screen" asp-route-criteria="@ScreenerConstants.NetNets">
                        Go to Screener <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                    </a>
                </h2>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingTwo">
            <h2 class="panel-title">
                <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                    Piotroski F-Score Screener
                </a>
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingTwo">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>
                    The Piotroski F-Score is a number going from 0 (the worst) to 9 (the best). It is used to measure the financial strengh of a company, using nine criterias. It is named after Joseph Piotroski, who invented it.
                </p>
                <br />
                <h4>How is it calculated?</h4>
                <p>The nine criterias are divided in three categories :</p>
                <div class="well">
                    <h4>Profitability :</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Net Income : one point is earned if the Net Income is positive in the current year</li>
                        <li>Cash From Operations : one point is earned if the Cash from Operations is positive in the current year</li>
                        <li>Quality of Earnings : one point is earned if the Cash from Operations is greater than the Net Income in the current year</li>
                        <li>Change in Return On Assets : one point is earned if the Returns On Assets (ROA) are greater this year than last year</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="well">
                    <h4>Capital Structure :</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Change in Long Term Leverage : one point is earned if the ratio Long Term Debt to Equity is lower this year than last year</li>
                        <li>Change in Current Ratio : one point is earned if the ratio Current Assets to Current Liabilities is greater this year than last year</li>
                        <li>Dilution : one point is earned if no new shares were issued during this year</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="well">
                    <h4>Operating Efficiency :</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Gross Margin : one point is earned if the Gross Margin is higher this year than last year</li>
                        <li>Change in Asset Turnover : one point is earned if the Asset Turnover is greater this year than last year</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>
                    <a style="text-decoration: none" asp-controller="Screener" asp-action="Screen" asp-route-criteria="@ScreenerConstants.Piotroski">
                        Go to Screener <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                    </a>
                </h2>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingThree">
            <h2 class="panel-title">
                <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
