                </a>
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseSeven" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingseven">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>Returns On Equity, aka ROE, is a measure of the capacity of the company to generate profits with the shareholders' money.</p>
                <p>It is simply the Net Income divided by the Total Equity of the company.</p>
                <p>If a company is leveraged, (lot of debts compared to equity), the comapny can have a high ROE, but a poor ROA. Therefore it is often interesting to compare both.</p>
                <p>This screener ranks companies according to their ROE, from highest to lowest.</p>
                <h2>
                    <a style="text-decoration: none" asp-controller="Screener" asp-action="Screen" asp-route-criteria="@ScreenerConstants.Roe">
                        Go to Screener <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                    </a>
                </h2>
            </div>
