    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingNine">
            <h2 class="panel-title">
                <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseNine" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseNine">
                    Returns On Invested Capital (ROIC) Screener
                </a>
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseNine" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingNine">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>Returns On Invested Capital, aka ROIC, tells us how good a company is using its own money.</p>
                <p>It is defined as the ratio of the Net Operating Profits After Taxes (NOPAT) divided by the Invested Capital (Total Assets - Non Interest Bearing Current Liabilities - Excess Cash).</p>
                <p>Of course, a higher ROIC is preferable to a lower one.</p>
                <p>This screener ranks companies according to their ROIC, from highest to lowest.</p>
                <h2>
                    <a style="text-decoration: none" asp-controller="Screener" asp-action="Screen" asp-route-criteria="@ScreenerConstants.Roic">
                        Go to Screener <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                    </a>
                </h2>
            </div>
